General.Name: Galileo Mining Ltd
General.Description: Galileo Mining Ltd engages in the exploration of mineral deposits in Western Australia. The company explores for cobalt, nickel, lithium, and copper, as well as nickel sulphides. It holds a 100% interest in the Norseman project that covers an area of 306 square kilometers located to the town of Norseman; and 67% interest Fraser Range Project covering an area of 602 square kilometers situated in the Albany-Fraser Orogen. The company was incorporated in 2003 and is based in West Perth, Australia.
General.Address: 13 Colin Street, West Perth, WA, Australia, 6005
